Sentencas: A-site deficiency perovskite oxides, Pr0.35Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta, and Pr(0.4)Sr(0.55)Co(0.2)Fe(0.7)Nb(0.1)O(3-delta )are prepared and act as the semiconductor for single-component fuel cell (SCFC) and reversible single-component cell (RSCC).
Titulo: Improving the performance of Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ-based single-component fuel cell and reversible single-component cells by manufacturing A-site deficiency

Sentencas: After reduction, the perovskite oxides can in situ exsolve Co3Fe7 alloy nanoparticles on perovskite and Ruddlesden-Popper structure oxide matrix, further facilitating the hydrogen oxidation reaction.
Titulo: Improving the performance of Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ-based single-component fuel cell and reversible single-component cells by manufacturing A-site deficiency

Sentencas: In addition, Pr(0.4)Sr(0.55)Co(0.2)Fe(0.7)Nb(0.1)O(3-delta )and reduced Pr0.4Sr0.55Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta have the most oxygen vacancies.
Titulo: Improving the performance of Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ-based single-component fuel cell and reversible single-component cells by manufacturing A-site deficiency

Sentencas: Furthermore, Pr0.4Sr0.55Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta based SCFC exhibits the highest cell performance and the mximum power densities (P-max) are 109.6, 145.2, and 211.1 mW cm(-2) at 600, 650, and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Improving the performance of Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ-based single-component fuel cell and reversible single-component cells by manufacturing A-site deficiency

Sentencas: It is because Pr0.4Sr0.55Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta shows the highest catalytic activity for oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) and the reduced Pr0.4Sr0.55Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta exhibits the highest catalytic activity for hydrogen oxidation reaction (HOR).
Titulo: Improving the performance of Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ-based single-component fuel cell and reversible single-component cells by manufacturing A-site deficiency

Sentencas: For RSCC, when 53%H-2-47%H2O fuel is applied and the P-max values are 105.7, 143.0, and 179.6 mW cm(-2) at 700, 650, and 600 degrees C, respectively in solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) mode and the current densities are -127.2, -205.8, and -265.0 mA cm(-2) under 1.3 V at 600, 650, and 700 degrees C, respectively in solid oxide electrolysis cell (SOEC) mode, indicating that Pr0.4Sr0.55Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-delta based RSCC can generate the most hydrogen in SOEC mode.
Titulo: Improving the performance of Pr0.4Sr0.6Co0.2Fe0.7Nb0.1O3-δ-based single-component fuel cell and reversible single-component cells by manufacturing A-site deficiency
